        Constructor. Every object on the Plot in PlotDesign must have an X and Y position determined from a MouseRelease event, and a height for calculating plant transition, shade, etc.
        Parameters:
        x - Horizontal position in plot.
        y - Vertical position in plot.
        height - Height in feet of plot object.
        radius - Radius in feet of plot object.
        imagePath - String of path to window view image.
        plotPath - String of path to plot design image.

                                  double viewWidth,
                                  double yearScale,
                                  javafx.scene.effect.Effect e)
        Abstract. All Plot Objects must specify how they will be drawn on the season view canvas.
        Parameters:
        gc - Graphics Context for drawing images/objects on canvas.
        gb - Blur effect for shade beneath plants.
        minScale - minimum scale amount for objects based on depth.
        maxDepth - Depth of plot design window.
        maxWidth - Width of plot design window.
        viewDepth - Depth of gc's canvas.
        viewWidth - Width of gc's Canvas.
        yearScale - Scaling amount based on year.
        e - Effect to be added to plants.
